history.content: Typical policy is that you email the professors in the semester before and ask if you can enroll in the course. Some grad courses like 270 are more accessible towards undergrad in the sense that there's enough seating, while others like 294-112 require you to fill out a form and have research experience.

Hi. I've basically taken almost all undergrad cs upper divs courses (except software engineering) and I want to progress to graduate level courses. What are all the ones I can get into? I'm not sure if I can get into many.

Thanks .
